        "body": "```bash\n$ grep \"mystical\" /home/moconnor/deepseek_tt_out.json -B2 | grep index\n      \"index\": 13,\n      \"index\": 14,\n      \"index\": 15,\n      \"index\": 16,\n      \"index\": 45,\n      \"index\": 46,\n      \"index\": 47,\n      \"index\": 48,\n      \"index\": 77,\n      \"index\": 78,\n      \"index\": 79,\n      \"index\": 80,\n      \"index\": 109,\n      \"index\": 110,\n      \"index\": 111,\n      \"index\": 112,\n      \"index\": 141,\n      \"index\": 142,\n      \"index\": 143,\n      \"index\": 144,\n      \"index\": 173,\n      \"index\": 174,\n      \"index\": 175,\n      \"index\": 176,\n      \"index\": 205,\n      \"index\": 206,\n      \"index\": 207,\n      \"index\": 208,\n      \"index\": 237,\n      \"index\": 238,\n      \"index\": 239,\n      \"index\": 240,\n```\n\nSo the last 4 users of every 16 get one output.\n\nIn fact for the 4 output categories above (32 A, 64 B, 64 C, 96 D) we see:\n\n```\n01-04: D (honor)\n05-08: B (fort)\n09-12: C (AABB)\n13-16: A (mystical)\n17-20: C (AABB)\n21-24: B (fort)\n25-32: D (honour)\n```\n\nSo whatever it is, it's already happening within one row of the mesh.",
